Merge pull request #17 from edx/mikix/site-cache

Notice when django cache is cleared

commit.message:
Notice when django cache is cleared

When Site.objects.clear_cache() is called, the SITE_CACHE variable
is reassigned to an empty dict. Our code wasn't noticing that, since
we imported the old variable directly.

Fix that by referencing SITE_CACHE indirectly.

Updated to version 2.3.0

Added conditional around redirect signal

We only setup the signal for the Redirect model if the requisite app is
installed. This ensures we avoid errors at startup for projects that do
not have the app installed.
